properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.default-health-endpoint
properties.description: Default health endpoint that will be checked to verify that a dependency is alive

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.dependencies
properties.description:
Mapping of alias to ZookeeperDependency. From Ribbon perspective the alias
 is actually serviceID since Ribbon can't accept nested structures in serviceID

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.instance-host
properties.description:
Predefined host with which a service can register itself in Zookeeper. Corresponds
 to the {code address} from the URI spec.

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.instance-port
properties.description: Port to register the service under (defaults to listening port)

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.metadata
properties.description:
Gets the metadata name/value pairs associated with this instance. This information
 is sent to zookeeper and can be used by other instances.

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.register
properties.description: Register as a service in zookeeper.

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.root
properties.description: Root Zookeeper folder in which all instances are registered

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.discovery.uri-spec
properties.description: The URI specification to resolve during service registration in Zookeeper

properties.name: spring.cloud.zookeeper.prefix
properties.description: Common prefix that will be applied to all Zookeeper dependencies' paths
